cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques to predict missing information about languages. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural networks, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper involves AI techniques to extract knowledge from the neural machine translation system, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. The paper also mentions the use of parallel texts, which could involve computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible category. Finally, the paper uses a massive many-to-one neural machine translation system, which could involve neural network architectures, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category.
